olive oil
20 g butter
1 packet jasmine rice
1 bag green beans
1 carrot
1 bag baby broccoli
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet pork mince
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
½ packet hoisin sauce
½ tbs soy sauce
½ tbs rice wine vinegar
1 pinch brown sugar
1 packet ginger paste
2 egg
2 clove garlic
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
1 tbs water (for the sauce)

• Finely chop garlic. In a medium saucepan, melt the butter and a dash of olive oil over a medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt and bring to the boil. Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

• Meanwhile, trim and halve green beans and baby broccoli. Thinly slice carrot into sticks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook green beans, baby broccoli and carrot until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add mixed sesame seeds and a drizzle of sesame oil and cook until fragrant, 30 seconds. Season to taste. Transfer veggies to a bowl. Cover to keep warm.

• Return frying pan to a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add crushed peanuts, hoisin sauce (see ingredients), the soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, brown sugar, ginger paste and water (for the sauce) and cook until bubbling, 30 seconds. Transfer to a bowl. Cover to keep warm.
• Wipe out frying pan, then return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Crack in the eggs and fry until the yolk is cooked to your liking, 4-5 minutes.

• Divide garlic rice and sesame veggies between plates.
• Top with Vietnamese-style pork and peanuts.
• Top with a fried egg to serve.